01/11/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A new class of 388 cadets graduated from the OSCE Police Service School in Kosovo on Saturday (30 October), bringing the number of trained multiethnic police officers to 6,925. The new class included 72 women. Addressing the graduates, UN Principal Deputy Special Representative to Kosovo Lawrence G. Rossin stressed that the police are key to preserving democracy and human rights in the province. (UN Web site - 30/10/04; OSCE Web site - 29/10/04)
